# Agentic QA — Project Rules

## After Every Code Change

Run `npm run check` after editing any file and fix all errors before finishing.
`npm run check` = `tsc --noEmit && next lint`
Never leave type errors or lint warnings in a response. Zero errors is the only acceptable state.

## Stack
Next.js 14 App Router · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS · HeroUI · next-intl (5 locales) · lucide-react · boring-avatars · ApexCharts · dayjs

## Architecture

**Frontend-only right now; backend is coming as a separate external service.**

- All data lives in `src/data/mockData.ts` — this is temporary scaffolding, not permanent
- When the backend arrives, `getMock*` helpers will be replaced with API client calls; types stay the same
- Never add Next.js API routes, server actions, or tRPC — the backend is external
- Never add React Query / SWR / Zustand / Redux — not needed yet

## Server / Client Split

Every `page.tsx` is a server component. It only does three things:
1. Extract route params
2. Call `useTranslations` to build a typed messages object
3. Pass that object as props to a `'use client'` sibling component

```tsx
// page.tsx — server only
export default function Page({ params }) {
  const t = useTranslations('MyFeature');
  const messages: MyFeatureMessages = { title: t('title') };
  return <MyFeatureClient projectId={params.projectId} messages={messages} />;
}
```

Never call `useTranslations` in a client component.

## Data Access Pattern

**Always use hooks — never import mockData directly in components.**

```ts
// ✅ Read via hook
import { useProject } from '@/hooks/useProject';
import { useRuns } from '@/hooks/useRuns';
const project = useProject(Number(projectId));
const runs    = useRuns(Number(projectId));

// ✅ Mutate (local state only)
const [items, setItems] = useState<RunType[]>(initialRuns);
setItems(prev => [...prev, newItem]);

// ❌ Never — don't import mockData directly in a component
import { getMockProject } from '@/src/data/mockData';
```

Hooks live in `hooks/use*.ts`. useMemo-wrapped, synchronous. When the backend arrives, only hooks change — components stay untouched.
Types in `types/` represent the future API response shape. Never add UI-only fields to entity types.

## Shared Utilities

Never define the same helper function twice. Shared logic goes in `utils/`:
- `rateColor(rate)` → `@/utils/rateColor` (used in 3+ pages, lives in utils once)

If a helper is used in one file only, define it at the bottom of that file. When it's needed elsewhere, extract it to `utils/`.

## Component Size Rule

Components over ~150 lines that mix data loading + state + multiple UI sections must be split:
- **Orchestrator** (~80–100 lines): hooks, state, handlers only — no large JSX blocks
- **Section components** (e.g. `RunHeader`, `RunInfoCard`, `RunCaseTable`): pure presentational, typed props

See `RunEditor.tsx` → `RunHeader/RunInfoCard/RunCaseTable` as the canonical reference.

## i18n

5 locales: `en · de · ja · pt-BR · zh-CN` — all must be updated together.
Missing a key in any locale file causes a runtime crash.
